Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
setRouteMode(25.10)                                        setRouteMode(25.10)

Name
       setRouteMode  -  Sets  global  parameters for the Early Global Route or
       earlyGlobalRoute

Syntax
       setRouteMode

       [-help]

       [-reset]

       [-earlyGlobalEffortLevel {standard | medium | low }]

       [-earlyGlobalHonorMsvRouteConstraint {true|false}]

       [-earlyGlobalNumTracksPerClockWire <value>]

       [-earlyGlobalReverseDirection "( <x1 y1 x2 y2> ) <Metal2:Metal2> (  <x3
       y3 x4 y4> ) <Metal3:Metal3 ...> "]

       [-earlyGlobalRoutePartitionAllowFeedthru <list_of_ptn_cell_names>]

       [-earlyGlobalRoutePartitionHonorFence <list_of_ptn_cell_names>]

       [-earlyGlobalRoutePartitionHonorPin <list_of_ptn_cell_names>]

       [-earlyGlobalRoutePartitionPinGuide {true|false}]

       [-earlyGlobalRouteSecondPG {true|false}]

       [-earlyGlobalRouteSelectedNetsOnly {true|false}]

       [-earlyGlobalRouteStripeLayerRange {<layerIdx1>:<layerIdx2>}]

       [-earlyGlobalSecondPGMaxFanout< integer>]

       Sets  global parameters for the Early Global Route or earlyGlobalRoute.
       The parameters that you specify with setRouteMode are then  used  auto-
       matically  whenever  you run the Early Global Router through the early-
       GlobalRoute command or internally during in-place optimization,  parti-
       tioning, or placement.

       The  setRouteMode  command parameter settings affect the results of the
       Early Global Router, which is run in all the steps during the  preRoute
       flow.  Consequently,  with  changes  in  these settings, the results of
       place_opt_design, ccopt_design, and postCTS will change.

       Note: If not required, it is best not to  change  the  tool  technology
       settings.

       Use  the  getRouteMode  command  to return the current settings for the
       setRouteMode command.

       Early Global Route supports nested partitions. The partitions specified
       with the  -earlyGlobalRoutePartitionHonorFence  and  the  -earlyGlobal-
       RoutePartitionHonorPin  parameters  are routed in the style that honors
       fence and pin constraints. All other partitions are routed

Parameters
       -earlyGlobalEffortLevel {standard| medium | low }
              Specifies the congestion effort level.

              Note: The low effort level value will reduce the  runtime  while
              standard effort level will increase the congestion accuracy

              * standard: Congestion is more accurate and runtime is larger.

              * medium:   Runtime  will  be much smaller and congestion report
                will have less accuracy.

              * low: Runtime is faster than medium but less accurate.

              Default: standard

              Note: While the setRouteMode  -earlyGlobalEffortLevel  parameter
              is mainly used for speed (low and medium will make it faster but
              less  accurate), the setDesignMode -congEffort parameter is used
              to increase optimization  effort  to  resolve  congestion.  Even
              though  these  parameters are not related directly, changing the
              Early Global Route effort level (decreasing it ) will change the
              results for the required congestion effort. Hence,  if  you  set
              the setDesignMode-congEffort as high, it is recommended that you
              keep the setRouteMode -earlyGlobalEffortLevel parameter at stan-
              dard (default) level.

              Data_type: enum, optional

       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes type and default in-
              formation for each setRouteMode parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man setRouteMode.

       -earlyGlobalHonorMsvRouteConstraint {true | false}
              Honors MSV domain constraints. This option  is  used  to  decide
              whether  Early Global Route  should honor power domain settings.

              By default, Early Global Route ignores the power domain settings
              and routes as flat design. When enabled, Early Global Route hon-
              ors power domain settings and route wires inside preferred power
              domain as much as possible.

              Default : false

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -earlyGlobalNumTracksPerClockWire value
              Specifies the special number of tracks per clock wires.

              Max: 8

              Min: 0

              Default: 0

              Data_type: int, optional

       -reset Restores all parameters modified using setRouteMode to their de-
              fault settings. The -reset parameter must be the first parameter
              specified.  If you specify -reset by itself, the software resets
              all setRouteMode parameters to  their  default  values.  If  you
              specify  parameters after -reset, the software resets only those
              parameters to their default values.

              Any values that do not already match the default value  and  are
              reset will be reported.

       -earlyGlobalReverseDirection
       Reverses  the  routing  direction  in the given region on the specified
       layer-range. It specifies an area in  which  the  Early  Global  Router
       routes wires in the non-preferred direction.

       Note:  You can define the reverse direction routing area by "(<x1 y1 x2
       y2>)" and routing layer by<  "Metal2:Metal2">.  In  release  16.1,  the
       Early Global Router only supports a single layer with this option. Con-
       sequently, <"Metal2:Metal3"> is not supported.

       The  -earlyGlobalReverseDirection parameter only has impact on the con-
       gestion value calculation. By routing on reverse direction, you can re-
       duce the routing capacity on the specified layer and  add  extract  re-
       source  on  the  above  and  below layers. Innovus does not display the
       routing wires in reverse direction routing region.

       For example, the following command reverses the  routing  direction  in
       the specified region on layer<Metal3>.

       setRouteMode  -earlyGlobalReverseDirection  "(757.996  542.697  995.323
       772.5685) Metal3:Metal3"

       The congestion value without reverse direction routing:

       Overflow after earlyGlobalRoute 0.02% H + 0.00% V

       The congestion value with reverse direction routing:

       earlyGlobalRoute overflow: 0.93% H + 0.10% V

       Default: ""

       Data_type: string, optional

       -earlyGlobalRoutePartitionAllowFeedthru <list_of_ptn_cell_names>
       Specifies the partition cell names for which the  Early  Global  Router
       honors partition fences.

       Default :  ""

       Data_type: string, optional

       -earlyGlobalRoutePartitionHonorFence <list_of_ptn_cell_names>
       Honors  partition fences with a single-entry constraint and also honors
       fixed pins. Under the single-entry constraint once a hierarchical route
       enters a partition fence it does not  cross  the  boundary  again.  The
       -earlyGlobalRoutePartitionHonorFence  parameter  routes a net belonging
       to more than one partition so that the routing does not violate  parti-
       tion boundaries, in addition to routing intra-partition and global nets
       using  the  specifications of the partitions. For example, if a net be-
       longs to partitions P1 and P3, but not P2, the net  is  routed  without
       going over the P2 partition boundary.

       Notes:

       * For flat partitioned designs, you can specify -earlyGlobalRouteParti-
         tionHonorFence to simulate channel-based routing. For channelless de-
         signs, you must perform feedthrough insertion before using this para-
         meter.

       * Supports designs with up to 180 partitions.

       * Early  Global Route supports nested partitions. The partitions speci-
         fied with the -earlyGlobalRoutePartitionHonorFence  and  the  -early-
         GlobalRoutePartitionHonorPin  parameters are routed in the style that
         honors fence and pin constraints. All  other  partitions  are  routed
         flat.

       Default :  ""

       Data_type: string, optional

       -earlyGlobalRoutePartitionHonorPin <list_of_ptn_cell_names>
       Honors  partition  fences with single-entry constraint and pre-assigned
       pins (pins marked  FIXED ) and assigned pins (pins marked  PLACED ).

       Default: ""

       Data_type: string, optional

       -earlyGlobalRoutePartitionPinGuide {true | false}
       Honors partition pin guides. It uses the pin guide  statements  in  the
       floorplan file to guide the routing through partition pin points.

       Note:  Fixed  pins  and  pin guides are only honored when -earlyGlobal-
       RoutePartitionPinGuide is true.

       Default: true

       Data_type: bool, optional

       -earlyGlobalRouteSecondPG {true | false}
       Specifies whether the secondary PG pin should be routed  or  not.  When
       enabled, it routes the pin specified by the setPGPinUseSignalRoute com-
       mand.

       Default: false

       Data_type: bool, optional

       -earlyGlobalRouteSelectedNetsOnly {true | false}
       Specifies  that  only the nets that are selected in the database are to
       be routed.

       Default: false

       Data_type: bool, optional

       -earlyGlobalRouteStripeLayerRange { <layerIdx1>:<layerIdx2>}
       Specifies the stripe layer range that is routed  to  the  secondary  PG
       pin.

       Default: " "

       Data_type: string, optional

       -earlyGlobalSecondPGMaxFanout <integer>
       Specifies the maximum fanout value during secondary PG pin routing.

       Max:INT_MAX

       Min:1

       Default: 2147483647

       Data_type: int, optional

Example
              * The  following command honors partition fences with single en-
                try and does not allow crossing other partitions, when  early-
                GlobalRoute is run:

                setRouteMode -earlyGlobalRoutePartitionHonorFence {.}

                earlyGlobalRoute

              * The  following command honors partition fences with single en-
                try and also honors placed pins, when earlyGlobalRoute is run:

                setRouteMode -earlyGlobalRoutePartitionHonorPin {.}

                earlyGlobalRoute

              * The following command resets all  setRouteMode  parameters  to
                their default values:

                setRouteMode -reset

Related Information
